  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nWhen working with Quarkus CLI, it may be desirable to have a separate maven settings file, but undesirable to have it as a default `/.m2/settings.xml`. For that case, it would be convenient to have an option, which will be work in a manner similar to `mvn -s settings.xml`.  \r\n\r\n### Implementation ideas\r\n\r\nSeveral:\r\n1. New option (`--maven-settings`) which accepts a path to a file, which is passed  to `mvn` command as `-s` option\r\n2. New option (`--maven-options`) which accepts a line with some maven options, which passed directly to `mvn`(e.g. `quarkus create app newapp --maven-options \"-s settings.xml -U -B\"`)\r\n3. Add options similar to 1. or 2. to `~/.quarkus/config.yaml` file",
